-- Cotton in New York Falls as Much as 3.9% to $1.4812 a Pound, Extends Slump
-- B y   S u p u n n a b u l   S u w a n n a k i j
-- 2010-12-23T02:06:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-23/cotton-in-new-york-falls-as-much-as-3-9-to-1-4812-a-pound-extends-slump.html
Cotton fell as much as 3.9 percent
to $1.4812 a pound in New York, after tumbling by the exchange
limit yesterday. The March-delivery contract traded at $1.4880
at 10:02 a.m. in Singapore.  ICE Futures U.S. raised the daily trading limit for cotton
futures to 6 cents a pound from 5 cents, effective today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
